==English==
===Etymology 1===
origin obscure

====Noun====
'''shack'''
# crude, roughly built [[hut]] or [[cabin]]
# {{US}} shiftless fellow; a low, itinerant beggar; a vagabond; a tramp.

=====Translations=====
*Spanish: [[choza]] {{f}}

====Verb====
'''to shack'''
# to [[live]] in or with
# to [[shack up]]
# to idle one's time away
# to wander as a vagabond or tramp.

===Etymology 2===
variant of ''[[shake]]''

====Noun====
'''shack'''
# grain to the ground and left after harvest.
# nuts which have fallen to the ground.
# freedom to pasturage in order to feed upon '''shack'''

====Verb====
'''to shack'''
# to shed or fall, as corn or grain at harvest.
# to feed in stubble, or upon waste corn.

